    </div>

    <p>This guide is part of our <a href="/candy/">candy and gummy hub</a>, which also covers <a href="/candy/vegan-gummy-bears/">vegan gummy bears</a>, <a href="/candy/vegan-sour-gummies/">vegan sour gummies</a>, and <a href="/candy/best-sour-gummies/">best sour gummies</a> across all types and brands.</p>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>The lördagsgodis tradition.</strong> In Sweden, candy is not an everyday indulgence — it is a Saturday ritual. Lördagsgodis (literally "Saturday candy") is a tradition dating to the 1950s when the Swedish government, concerned about dental health, encouraged families to limit candy consumption to one day per week. The result? Swedes developed one of the most sophisticated candy cultures in the world, spending more per capita on confectionery than nearly any other nation — but eating it mindfully, once a week. This cultural pressure created an industry obsessed with quality, variety, and premium ingredients. Every Swedish gummy on this list reflects that legacy.
    </div>

